        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "GCI < 5% on QoI across all operating points",
        "description": "Grid convergence index computed via Richardson extrapolation on three systematically refined meshes. Mean GCI on relative hemolysis index QoI must be below 5% at all five operating points."
      },
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (1.2M, 4.8M, 12.1M polyhedral cells) were simulated at all five flow-speed operating points. Richardson extrapolation yields a mean GCI of 2.3% on the hemolysis QoI and 1.8% on pressure head, both below the 5% acceptance threshold. Apparent order of convergence is 1.94, consistent with second-order discretization."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou1-tc-04",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou1-tc-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "In-vitro test conditions documented and matched to CFD boundary conditions",
        "description": "Experimental flow loop conditions (fluid temperature, hematocrit, inlet flow rate, rotational speed) are documented with measurement uncertainty and reproduced as CFD boundary conditions within stated tolerances."
      },
      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments were conducted using bovine blood at 37°C with 33% hematocrit. Flow rates and rotational speeds at all five operating points are documented in the test report (TR-CBP-2024-003) with calibrated uncertainty of ±1.5% on flow rate and ±0.3% on rotational speed. CFD boundary conditions replicate these values within measurement uncertainty bounds."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou1-oc-05",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/morrison-cou1-oc-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Quantitative agreement metric: normalized RMS error < 15% on hemolysis index and pressure head",
        "description": "Normalized root-mean-square error between CFD predictions and experimental measurements of relative hemolysis index and pump pressure head must be below 15% across all five operating conditions."
      },
      "rationale": "Normalized RMS error on relative hemolysis index is 8.4% and on pressure head is 6.1% across the five operating points, both well within the 15% acceptance threshold. Systematic bias is less than 3% at all conditions. Achieved Gradation 3 because quantitative uncertainty-aware comparison (area validation metric per Oberkampf & Barone) was also performed, confirming model adequacy."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou1-rqi-06",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
