        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI directly maps to clinical decision criterion",
        "description": "The primary QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) is the same metric used in the regulatory submission acceptance criterion (RH < 1.0 vs. predicate device), demonstrating direct relevance."
      },
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) computed by the CFD model is the identical metric specified in the regulatory acceptance criterion for the Class II CPB device submission. The QoI is not a surrogate; it is the direct decision variable. This direct mapping satisfies Gradation 2 relevance requirements without further justification."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou1-rva-07",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
